\section{PROOF CONTEXTS}
=DOC
	val Ûcomp_pcÝ		: PROOF_CONTEXT
	val Ûcomp_epcÝ	: EPROOF_CONTEXT
=DESCRIBE
These are the unevaluated and evaluated forms of a proof context which
is obtained from $pair\_pc$ (q.v.) by adding entries to the rewriting
context corresponding to the following conversions:
=GFT
div_conv	¾_conv		greater_conv		¼_conv
lt_conv		mod_conv	minus_conv		plus_conv
times_conv	char_eq_conv	string_eq_conv
=TEX
Thus rewriting using this proof context will cause evaluation of all sub-terms
of the form
=GFT
	a op b
=TEX
where $¬a®$ and $¬b®$ are literals and where $op$ is either $=$ or
one of the standard natural number operations.

For example, after executing:
=GFT Example
push_proof_context comp_epc;
=TEX
the calls:
=GFT Example
rewrite_conv[]
	¬if "a" = "b" then (7 * 11 * 13) + 3 else (7 + 11 + 13) * 3®;
rewrite_conv[length_def]
	¬if Length [1;2] = 2 then (7 * 11 * 13) + 3 else (7 + 11 + 13) * 3®;
=TEX
will return the following theorems:
=GFT Example
ô (if "a" = "b" then 7 * 11 * 13 + 3 else (7 + 11 + 13) * 3) = 93
ô (if Length [1; 2] = 2 then 7 * 11 * 13 + 3 else (7 + 11 + 13) * 3) = 1004
=TEX
=ENDDOC
